    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "actually slice is correct; it's `convert` which is the problem here. the data in `slice(a, 0, 1)` has dirty bytes.\r\nin binary it looks like\r\n```\r\nlength | data\r\n0x01   | 0x6162\r\n```\r\nwhen converted to `bytes32`, the dirty bytes do not get zero-padded.",
